# CambiOS code ownership.
#
# Paths listed here REQUIRE a code-owner review before a PR can merge (paired with
# branch protection: require_code_owner_reviews=true). The cambios-agent bot is
# intentionally NOT an owner, so it cannot self-merge changes to these paths — an
# owner (a human, or a review agent acting as one) must approve first.
#
# Unlisted paths the bot MAY auto-merge on green CI, hands-off:
#   - docs/ (except docs/adr/) — STATUS.md, ASSUMPTIONS.md, design docs
#   - verification/ — test/proof additions  (see note below)
#   - user/ — the hands-off USERSPACE-BUILD lane (looser rules than kernel)

# Verified kernel core
/src/                 @riccajason

# Syscall ABI surface (the kernel/userspace contract)
/cambios-abi/         @riccajason

# Architecture decision records (authoritative history)
/docs/adr/            @riccajason

# Project operating contract
/CLAUDE.md            @riccajason

# The gates themselves: build, lint, hooks, CI
/Makefile             @riccajason
/tools/               @riccajason
/.github/             @riccajason

# Conscious exceptions (NOT owned, so the bot auto-merges them on green CI):
#   user/        — Jason's hands-off USERSPACE-BUILD lane. Add here to require review.
#   verification/— hands-off test/proof drains. NOTE: a bot could in principle make
#                  a proof vacuous and keep CI green; add `/verification/ @riccajason`
#                  if that risk outweighs hands-off proof draining.
